  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Build the Printer Cabinet Carcass",
      "body": "Drill 3/4\" pocket holes on the top and sides of the 3/4\" plywood and attach it to the 2x2 legs with 1-1/4\" pocket hole screws and wood glue. Note that the plywood panels are flush to the interior edge of the legs.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/cb4c9e33e0b3307e.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add the Desk Aprons and Legs",
      "body": "Drill 3/4\" pocket holes into the 1x6s and 1x2s and attach to the printer cabinet carcass with 1-1/4\" pocket hole screws and wood glue. All boards are flush to the interior edges of the legs.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/9ba6c9a5b19f2d61.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Attach the Shelf",
      "body": "Drill 3/4\" pocket holes around all underside edges of the 3/4\" plywood shelf. Attach the shelf to the printer cabinet carcass with 1-1/4\" pocket hole screws and wood glue. Attach the 1x2 trim to the shelf with 1-1/4\" pocket holes and wood glue.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e2b5df1f4d5eb170.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Build the Printer Tray",
      "body": "Attach the 1x2 slide support to the right side of the printer cabinet carcass with 1-1/4\" brad nails and wood glue. Build the tray by attaching the 1x2 back and sides to the 3/4\" plywood bottom with 1-1/4\" brad nails and wood glue. Install the drawer slides according to manufacturer's directions.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/68f13231b3841586.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add the Printer Cabinet Door",
      "body": "Route a 1/8\" deep groove into the 3/4\" plywood door to mimic two faux drawer fronts. Attach door to printer cabinet with hinges. Attach drawer knobs or pulls.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/cb7b58b5eb7ca791.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Build the Drawers",
      "body": "For the drawer backs, rip a 1x4 board down to 3\" wide. Next, route a 1/4\" deep groove into the 1x4 drawer fronts and sides. Drill 3/4\" pocket holes on the outsides of the drawer fronts and backs (pocket holes will be hidden by drawer face in the next step). Construct the drawer boxes with 1-1/4\" pocket hole screws. The 1/4\" plywood drawer bottom will slide into the grooves in the front and sides. Attach the bottom panel to the back with 3/4\" brad nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/631698a899f368c8.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Attach the Drawer Faces",
      "body": "Attach the drawer faces to the drawer boxes with 1-1/4\" screws. Install drawer knobs or pulls.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/9dc391af35808792.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Install Drawers and Drawer Slides",
      "body": "Install 18\" drawer slides according to manufacturer's directions.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/ede271c5e7d23948.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Attach the Top",
      "body": "Attach the top with 1-1/4\" pocket holes and wood glue. Pre-drill and countersink pilot holes above the 3 front legs and drive 1-1/4\" wood screws down into the legs. Allow for a 1\" overhang on all sides. To hide the raw plywood edges, iron on 3/4\" veneer edge banding.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/b43783d89336a234.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Visit JenWoodhouse.com",
      "body": "For more free building plans and DIY project ideas, visit JenWoodhouse.com.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/885026627a8da0e6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Finishing Steps",
      "body": "Sand, stain or paint, and finish as desired.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/6d05ecc6fa18c237.webp"
    }
  ],
